name: integer_i32_sign_extended_i16_minimum
description: |
  This is i16 minimum represented as i32, requiring the upper
  16 bits to be set during sign extension. It catches zero-extension,
  partial-register, and widening-conversion bugs while preserving the value
  -32768.
format: hex
decode-as: i32-le
pair:
  - with: ../i16/minimum.input
    hint: equal
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i32"
  - "sign-extension"
  - "conversion"
  - "lower-width"
  - "two's-complement"
---
00 80 ff ff   # -32768
